# Copy to .devcontainer/.env (gitignored) before `docker compose up` or opening
# the dev container. Phase 0 auth is a repo-scoped, short-lived API key injected
# at RUNTIME only — never baked into an image, never a host secret mount.
#
#   cp .devcontainer/.env.example .devcontainer/.env
#   # then edit .env and set a real key
#
# NOTE: values here land in the container env and are visible via `docker
# inspect`. This is adequate for LOCAL Phase 0 dev only; a real secrets store is
# a later-phase concern.
#
# ⚠ DO NOT put BROKER_GITHUB_TOKEN in this file. This .env is the CODER's env_file,
# and the coder must hold NO push token. The Phase 2 broker receives its token via
# host-shell interpolation instead — `export BROKER_GITHUB_TOKEN=ghs_xxx` before
# `docker compose up` (see docs/devcontainer-phase2.md).

ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-REPLACE_ME
